@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@
+# Solution
+
+Successful `get` calls returned values without moving their entries to the
+most-recently-used end of the `OrderedDict`, so later inserts evicted recently
+read keys. The cache now refreshes recency after a valid lookup.
+
+`put` also evicted an entry whenever the cache was full, even when the key
+already existed. Eviction is now performed only for a new key, allowing an
+existing entry to be updated and promoted without removing another entry.
